        {
          "text": "In the coders channel, a developer introduced a multi-agent orchestrator built in Python using the claude-agent-sdk, featuring an A2A-protocol read-only research agent with tools including Tavily, DuckDuckGo, fetch, and arXiv via MCP. The developer requested permission to test the agent in a sandbox channel on the server, specifying it would be read-only, send no DMs, and only respond to direct mentions. They also mentioned having emailed inquiries@elizalabs.ai and asked about OAuth invite or whitelist access. Odilitime, a core moderator and developer, responded directing the user to DM them regarding the OAuth process.",
